WEBVTT

00:05.089 --> 00:07.591
WHILE THIS STORY IS BASED
ON ACTUAL EVENTS,

00:07.675 --> 00:11.345
CERTAIN CHARACTERS, INCIDENTS,
AND DIALOGUE WERE FICTIONALIZED.

00:11.429 --> 00:14.932
ANY SIMILARITY TO ANY PERSON,
LIVING OR DEAD, IS FOR DRAMATIC PURPOSES.

00:27.445 --> 00:29.655
<i>Do me a favor, enjoy life.</i>

00:29.739 --> 00:32.324
<i>And if someone offers you drugs,</i>
<i>just say no.</i>

01:25.669 --> 01:27.671
MARADONA:
BLESSED DREAM

01:28.047 --> 01:29.423
BROKEN

01:34.303 --> 01:37.097
BARCELONA, SPAIN.

01:37.181 --> 01:39.433
<i>McEnroe is making ads for Rolex.</i>

01:39.517 --> 01:42.561
Didn't we come to conquer Europe, big guy?

01:42.645 --> 01:46.232
McEnroe wasn't sidelined
by hepatitis for three months.

01:46.899 --> 01:50.486
- You're blaming the hepatitis?
- And your shitty attitude.

01:50.820 --> 01:53.864
No sponsor wants a guy
who fights with everyone.

01:53.948 --> 01:56.826
Because McEnroe is Mother Teresa? Come on.

01:56.909 --> 02:00.663
Why are you going on about him?
Why don't you hire his manager?

02:00.746 --> 02:03.833
I might. At least,
he can walk like a normal person.

02:03.916 --> 02:07.586
- He's more stupid than usual.
- Why are you so cranky?

02:07.670 --> 02:09.171
- What's wrong?
- I don't know.

02:09.255 --> 02:12.383
How is it I make so much money,
but it always vanishes?

02:12.466 --> 02:13.926
You make me do this bullshit.

02:14.009 --> 02:17.304
Wait, it's not my fault your money's gone.

02:17.388 --> 02:20.724
I've told you to reduce
your expenses, but you won't listen.

02:20.808 --> 02:22.977
Do you know how much
you've spent on calls?

02:23.060 --> 02:25.271
My family lives fucking miles away.

02:25.354 --> 02:28.148
Your siblings recount
<i>Chavo </i> episodes over the phone.

02:28.232 --> 02:30.651
What do you expect?
They don't carry it here.

02:30.776 --> 02:33.612
It's an international call.
It costs a fortune.

02:33.696 --> 02:36.615
I'm Diego Maradona.
If I can't call, something's wrong.

02:36.699 --> 02:39.743
It's the phone, your millionaire habits,

02:39.827 --> 02:42.079
the money you send to your parents,

02:42.204 --> 02:45.040
and providing for those
ten bums living with you.

02:45.124 --> 02:48.252
Don't mention my friends!
I'd be depressed without them.

02:48.335 --> 02:49.420
Call a taxi.

02:49.503 --> 02:51.839
- You get in.
- A taxi?

02:51.922 --> 02:54.008
I'll pay, what's the problem?

02:54.091 --> 02:56.218
- Go fuck yourself.
- You go fuck yourself.

02:56.302 --> 02:58.095
No, you go fuck yourself.

03:15.946 --> 03:20.367
Damn, he looks like a pederast
in that painting. Look at those lips.

03:20.451 --> 03:22.411
I prefer his usual ass face.

03:22.494 --> 03:24.330
Stop it, don't make me laugh.

03:24.413 --> 03:27.875
He does look a bit like a degenerate,
you're right.

03:29.168 --> 03:30.544
Let's get out of here.

03:30.628 --> 03:33.255
No, you have to make peace with this man.

03:34.548 --> 03:36.467
I've heard that his wife's nice.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.886
I hope so,
or I'll be bored to death.

03:40.304 --> 03:42.139
What a nice house.

03:42.222 --> 03:44.266
- Yes, too fancy.
- Is that bad?

03:44.683 --> 03:46.477
It smells like old people.

03:47.603 --> 03:50.439
- Shut up, you're so critical.
- Yes.

03:51.440 --> 03:56.445
Oh, no. They set the table for three.
I wasn't invited. This is embarrassing.

03:56.946 --> 03:58.364
Hello.

03:59.281 --> 04:01.116
Yes. Thank you.

04:03.285 --> 04:04.536
Thank you very much.

04:05.537 --> 04:07.915
- Diego, Claudia, darling.
- Hi.

04:09.708 --> 04:11.418
- Thanks for coming.
- How are you?

04:11.502 --> 04:12.753
I'm fine.

04:12.836 --> 04:14.755
- You look beautiful.
- Thank you.

04:14.838 --> 04:15.923
You were invited.

04:16.006 --> 04:19.635
She saw three plates
and thought she wasn't invited.

04:19.718 --> 04:24.098
Yes. It'll only be the three of us,
because my wife's feeling unwell.

04:25.140 --> 04:26.225
What a shame.

04:26.308 --> 04:30.020
Listen, I have an exquisite
Chambord Liqueur Royale.

04:35.275 --> 04:36.193
Thank you.

04:41.782 --> 04:45.744
Lord, bless this food
that we're about to eat

04:45.828 --> 04:48.414
and grant that there may be
no hunger in the world.

04:49.206 --> 04:50.040
Amen.

04:50.249 --> 04:51.333
- Amen.
- Amen.

04:53.335 --> 04:54.336
They're oysters.

04:56.005 --> 04:56.964
Enjoy your meal.

05:03.804 --> 05:08.976
You could say that a big part of my temper
is due to my mother.

05:09.059 --> 05:11.228
A cantankerous Biscayan.

05:11.812 --> 05:13.313
I was born in Bilbao,

05:13.439 --> 05:17.443
but I lived in the town of Baracaldo,
famous for its ladies' handball.

05:18.360 --> 05:19.445
How interesting.

05:19.528 --> 05:21.363
The shrimp is from Palamós.

05:21.864 --> 05:23.407
You can use your hands.

05:23.490 --> 05:25.993
- My hands?
- Yes, certainly.

05:28.037 --> 05:31.248
Well, eventually, I disobeyed my father

05:31.331 --> 05:33.208
who wanted me to be a lawyer.

05:33.292 --> 05:36.086
Instead, I worked
in the construction business,

05:36.170 --> 05:39.173
so I was able to dedicate myself

05:39.256 --> 05:41.759
to my other great passion,
which is soccer.

05:42.426 --> 05:43.427
You'll like that.

05:44.344 --> 05:48.390
Football Club Barcelona is
not only a great showcase for soccer,

05:48.474 --> 05:53.187
but it's also a model club
in terms of family values and behavior.

05:53.270 --> 05:57.191
As the president,
I've been in the public eye for years.

05:57.274 --> 05:59.193
And I've never had any scandals,

05:59.276 --> 06:03.280
nor rumors of affairs with women
other than my wife.

06:07.409 --> 06:10.162
I often see myself reflected
in your outbursts,

06:10.245 --> 06:13.165
but, in public,
my reactions are different,

06:13.248 --> 06:15.709
as I have to look after
the interests of the club.

06:15.793 --> 06:19.088
But I listened to you,
and I fired Udo Lattek.

06:19.171 --> 06:22.466
So, when you recover from hepatitis,
you'll feel comfortable.

06:22.883 --> 06:25.594
- The papers say otherwise.
- Really? What?

06:25.677 --> 06:30.682
They say Schuster called Lattek
a "fucking drunk,"

06:30.766 --> 06:34.561
and Lattek told you to choose
between Schuster or him,

06:34.645 --> 06:35.854
and you chose Schuster.

06:35.938 --> 06:38.732
Well, the press twists everything.

06:39.191 --> 06:41.110
You're telling me.

06:41.527 --> 06:44.947
Your journalist friends are saying
I had... What was it?

06:45.030 --> 06:47.241
- Gonorrhea.
- Gonorrhea instead of hepatitis.

06:48.492 --> 06:51.912
I admit that I've been wrong
about you sometimes, Diego.

06:51.995 --> 06:55.457
But it's just that when I feel undermined,

06:55.541 --> 06:57.876
I get carried away
by my Basque temperament.

06:58.293 --> 07:00.879
Anyway, we have to start getting along.

07:01.880 --> 07:04.133
That's why I decided to come tonight.

07:04.675 --> 07:08.762
I suppose you're happy to have
a coach to your liking, like Menotti.

07:09.138 --> 07:12.850
I'm sure he'll let you sleep in
on game days.

07:13.892 --> 07:15.310
He knows me well.

07:16.061 --> 07:17.771
- Well, then, let's toast.
- Sure.

07:17.896 --> 07:20.691
To a season full of success.

07:20.774 --> 07:22.151
- Okay, cheers.
- Cheers.

07:28.782 --> 07:30.659
<i>How are you? How do you feel?</i>

07:31.201 --> 07:33.245
- Dying to play.
- Of course.

07:33.328 --> 07:37.124
But I'm also worried,
because hepatitis took its toll on me.

07:37.207 --> 07:39.293
I'm afraid I won't get back to my level.

07:39.376 --> 07:41.587
Don't worry, I brought you the best.

07:41.670 --> 07:44.131
Professor, I need you for a minute.

07:45.215 --> 07:48.802
Professor Signorini is a rarity in soccer.

07:48.886 --> 07:52.431
He looks more like a university professor
than a physical trainer.

07:54.057 --> 07:56.602
I want to introduce you to a new kid.

07:57.519 --> 07:59.354
Nice to meet you.

07:59.438 --> 08:02.649
Explain to him
your research on biorhythms.

08:02.733 --> 08:05.027
Yes, there's a very interesting theory

08:05.110 --> 08:08.906
that says that we have
rhythmic biological cycles.

08:09.031 --> 08:12.826
And they affect us in different ways.
Emotionally, physically.

08:14.203 --> 08:17.539
<i>I want to see what your body has to say</i>
<i>and work on that.</i>

08:17.623 --> 08:19.082
<i>Your body has a lot to say.</i>

08:19.499 --> 08:22.044
I hope that my body speaks better
than I do.

08:22.127 --> 08:25.172
Every time I open my mouth,
I get into all kinds of trouble.

08:26.298 --> 08:28.175
- Thank you.
- Please, excuse me.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.636
While you're getting ready, Diego,

08:30.719 --> 08:32.638
I need your help with the team.

08:33.597 --> 08:36.725
It's like they're afraid to play.
They have no confidence.

08:36.808 --> 08:39.770
I want them to get the ball,
to keep it, to play.

08:39.853 --> 08:42.814
- Help me with that.
- Of course, César, I will.

08:42.898 --> 08:45.776
Just be patient. Lattek was training

08:45.859 --> 08:47.903
- soldiers instead of players.
- Yes.

08:57.371 --> 09:00.832
<i>Barcelona is taking the field</i>
<i>for this latest game.</i>

09:00.916 --> 09:02.501
<i>They're up against Real Betis.</i>

09:02.584 --> 09:07.381
<i>Diego's doing his warm-up exercises</i>
<i>before the start of the game.</i>

09:07.506 --> 09:09.049
<i>Diego!</i>

09:09.132 --> 09:10.717
<i>Lots support in the stands.</i>

09:10.801 --> 09:13.345
<i>Both club presidents are in the box,</i>

09:13.428 --> 09:16.265
<i>and César Luis Menotti</i>
<i>makes his debut with Barcelona.</i>

09:21.603 --> 09:23.605
<i>After being sidelined for so long,</i>

09:23.689 --> 09:26.608
<i>stepping onto the field is</i>
<i>like living again,</i>

09:26.692 --> 09:29.152
<i>but my legs weigh a hundred pounds.</i>

09:29.653 --> 09:32.781
<i>I barely touch two balls</i>
<i>and already regret being there.</i>

09:32.864 --> 09:34.491
<i>I can't handle the contact.</i>

09:38.745 --> 09:42.332
<i>I'm as predictable as the next player.</i>

09:42.416 --> 09:45.002
<i>Menotti kept me in out of respect.</i>

09:45.085 --> 09:46.837
<i>I should have gone after five.</i>

09:54.261 --> 09:56.263
<i>I've never experienced that before.</i>

09:57.556 --> 09:59.766
<i>The crowd started to whistle at me.</i>

09:59.850 --> 10:02.311
<i>Be patient. What does Menotti say?</i>

10:02.394 --> 10:05.564
He says that the magic will come back,

10:05.897 --> 10:08.817
that I shouldn't worry,
but it's only to encourage me.

10:08.900 --> 10:10.861
<i>Why would he? Trust him, son.</i>

10:11.278 --> 10:12.904
<i>I can go back to the mill.</i>

10:13.280 --> 10:16.116
Dad, just because I'm having
a hard time doesn't mean

10:16.199 --> 10:20.787
we'll go back to Fiorito,
and you'll go back to work at the mill.

10:21.246 --> 10:22.247
Diego!

10:22.664 --> 10:23.665
Diego!

10:25.334 --> 10:26.585
Will you stop training?

10:27.377 --> 10:31.256
Professor Signorini told you
not to overdo it.

10:32.257 --> 10:36.345
Look at you, all sweaty. Let go!

10:37.554 --> 10:40.640
Stop it. Come on.

10:40.724 --> 10:42.601
What's all this?

10:44.686 --> 10:45.979
You didn't ask Claudia?

10:46.355 --> 10:49.775
We're going hunting 200 miles from here.

10:49.858 --> 10:53.528
If we leave now, we'll get there tonight
and be back tomorrow.

10:53.612 --> 10:55.447
No, it's fine. Go.

10:55.947 --> 10:58.158
Go. It'll be good for you
to have some fun.

10:58.241 --> 10:59.117
- Really?
- Yes.

10:59.201 --> 11:00.744
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

11:00.827 --> 11:02.621
- Don't forget to shower.
- Okay.

11:06.708 --> 11:08.877
Galindez, why are you all dressed up?

11:09.795 --> 11:11.922
It's the nightclub's anniversary.

11:12.422 --> 11:14.299
Are you going for a jog or something?

11:26.353 --> 11:28.939
You set this whole sham up
to go to a nightclub?

11:31.316 --> 11:34.403
The shotguns, the coolers,
the outfits, everything.

11:34.486 --> 11:36.571
All a show to fool me?

11:36.655 --> 11:38.949
How can you be such an asshole, Diego?

11:39.032 --> 11:41.410
Why are you dressed like that, Galindez?

11:42.452 --> 11:44.788
Don't you remember
we were going hunting today?

11:45.163 --> 11:46.915
Oh, that was today.

11:46.998 --> 11:49.626
No, there's no need. That's it.

11:50.293 --> 11:52.671
I may look like I'm stupid, but I'm not.

11:52.754 --> 11:54.464
Hold on a sec, honey.

11:54.798 --> 11:59.428
Did you arrange all this bullshit
to drag me into a nightclub? You know me.

12:17.446 --> 12:19.197
You're such an asshole, Galindez.

12:19.781 --> 12:23.034
I'm gonna kick your ass
back to Buenos Aires.

12:27.414 --> 12:28.957
Okay.

12:32.002 --> 12:33.503
Where's your little foot?

12:35.380 --> 12:37.382
- Are you waiting for a client?
- No.

12:38.008 --> 12:39.426
Don't answer.

12:39.509 --> 12:41.178
Carlos, stop being paranoid.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.888
They're looking for me.

12:42.971 --> 12:46.016
Who? It's better to lose you
than to find you.

12:47.184 --> 12:48.852
Cut me a line.

12:48.935 --> 12:51.688
Want me to paint your nails
or cut you a line?

12:51.771 --> 12:52.689
Both.

13:01.615 --> 13:02.824
Give me that.

13:03.575 --> 13:06.161
Be patient.

13:07.996 --> 13:10.832
Here, here, here.

13:21.635 --> 13:22.594
I'll go see.

13:28.099 --> 13:29.059
Who is it?

13:29.684 --> 13:33.063
Mauricio Mendez, journalist
from the<i> Primicias </i> newspaper.

13:33.271 --> 13:35.065
I'm looking for Carlos Ferro Viera.

13:35.148 --> 13:38.944
No, you have the wrong address.
I don't know anyone by that name.

13:39.027 --> 13:40.654
You're Marilú, aren't you?

13:40.737 --> 13:43.698
I'm a friend of Valverde's,
Tano Valverde, from Caix.

13:44.533 --> 13:46.576
How did Carlos screw up this time?

13:46.660 --> 13:48.745
Well, I'd like to know that, too.

13:49.037 --> 13:51.998
He has an arrest warrant out
for the Maradona case.

13:53.083 --> 13:55.877
- I have no idea where he is.
- Okay.

13:56.461 --> 13:58.880
Look, I'm going to give you my number,

14:00.006 --> 14:03.260
in case he gets in touch.
It's for an interview,

14:03.385 --> 14:06.888
so he can tell us what happened
to Diego before his hospitalization.

14:07.264 --> 14:09.933
To be clear, there's no risk involved.

14:10.308 --> 14:13.395
Will you pay for it?
People charge for stories now.

14:13.478 --> 14:15.689
It depends on what Carlos has to say.

14:16.106 --> 14:17.524
If he gets in touch,

14:17.607 --> 14:20.318
not that I think he will,
I'll tell him about this.

14:20.652 --> 14:22.112
Okay. All right.

14:39.713 --> 14:41.214
Hello.

15:13.705 --> 15:15.290
I'll come with you.

15:43.443 --> 15:45.862
<i>A new round in this Spanish league.</i>

15:45.945 --> 15:49.449
<i>Barcelona Football Club is</i>
<i>on the field and there is Diego.</i>

15:49.532 --> 15:52.327
<i>El Flaco Menotti is on the bench,</i>

15:52.410 --> 15:55.872
<i>waiting for everything</i>
<i>to unravel just as planned.</i>

15:59.584 --> 16:02.796
<i>A pass to Maradona,</i>
<i>and it's a goal for Barcelona.</i>

16:02.879 --> 16:03.963
<i>Diego Maradona.</i>

16:04.047 --> 16:08.385
<i>Maradona lines it up, he aims,</i>
<i>he kicks the ball into the goal.</i>

16:08.468 --> 16:10.637
<i>Goal for Barca at the start of the game.</i>

16:10.720 --> 16:12.806
<i>The ball is up, Maradona has it,</i>

16:12.889 --> 16:16.935
<i>and excellent kick by Maradona,</i>
<i>great skill from the Argentine.</i>

16:17.852 --> 16:20.271
<i>Maradona enters the area</i>

16:20.355 --> 16:23.400
<i>and kicks the ball to the goal.</i>
<i>Goal for Barcelona.</i>

16:27.070 --> 16:30.365
<i>He lines up for the kick.</i>
<i>Diego Maradona shoots,</i>

16:30.448 --> 16:32.325
<i>and the ball bounces off the post.</i>

16:32.784 --> 16:37.038
<i>A pass to the goal area and a header.</i>
<i>It's Maradona and goal.</i>

16:37.122 --> 16:40.166
<i>Goal for Barca, Diego Armando Maradona.</i>

16:41.251 --> 16:45.672
<i>Maradona shoots, evading two,</i>
<i>a double dribble, a pass to Carrasco,</i>

16:45.755 --> 16:50.677
<i>and Maradona shoots,</i>
<i>goal for Barcelona, Maradona.</i>

16:59.686 --> 17:04.899
If we have learned anything from Diego,
it's that together we are invincible.

17:05.233 --> 17:08.528
Therefore, in FC Barcelona, we are all,

17:08.611 --> 17:12.782
players and managers, after the same goal,
to win the Copa del Rey.

17:12.949 --> 17:17.454
Diego, isn't it risky, a few days
before a final against Real Madrid,

17:17.537 --> 17:20.957
for you and Schuster to go to Germany
to play a exhibition game?

17:21.040 --> 17:24.627
It is a commitment
that we made a while ago,

17:24.711 --> 17:27.505
and we are proud to participate

17:27.589 --> 17:30.258
in a tribute to a great player
like Paul Breitner.

17:30.341 --> 17:31.509
Fans are worried.

17:31.593 --> 17:35.138
They shouldn't worry
because in games like this,

17:35.430 --> 17:38.183
there are no injuries
or physical wear and tear.

17:38.266 --> 17:41.227
Fans can feel reassured, I mean,

17:41.352 --> 17:43.855
the board of directors has just ruled

17:43.938 --> 17:47.400
against giving the players permission
to attend this event.

17:48.026 --> 17:50.904
Why, boss?
A few days ago, you said we could go.

17:50.987 --> 17:53.615
I know, Diego,
but it's the board's decision.

17:53.698 --> 17:55.617
I can't go over their heads.

17:55.992 --> 17:57.869
Núñez, don't be ridiculous,

17:57.952 --> 18:02.248
everybody knows you choose
the brand of toilet paper at the stadium.

18:02.332 --> 18:06.669
Well, the board doesn't need
to be involved in that kind of decision.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.797
President, what's the decision?

18:08.880 --> 18:12.342
Maradona said he'd be
at Paul Breitner's farewell and he will.

18:12.425 --> 18:13.510
Thank you very much.

18:17.722 --> 18:20.225
<i>Should I pass it to you or Schuster?</i>

18:27.023 --> 18:28.691
<i>Come on, more rhythm, guys.</i>

18:28.775 --> 18:30.360
Can I ask you a question?

18:31.194 --> 18:33.571
Did you borrow money from Flaco Menotti?

18:34.864 --> 18:36.825
Where did you get that from?

18:36.908 --> 18:38.743
I read it in a gossip magazine.

18:39.327 --> 18:40.411
Is it true?

18:41.371 --> 18:42.539
It's not a loan.

18:43.581 --> 18:46.000
Flaco is a long-time friend. He offered.

18:46.751 --> 18:49.337
It's an investment to finish the film.

18:53.466 --> 18:56.344
How are the numbers going?
Diego is worried.

18:56.928 --> 18:59.138
- Did he send you to ask me?
- No, not at all.

18:59.222 --> 19:00.431
Doesn't Diego trust me?

19:00.515 --> 19:02.976
Claudia, you know me,
I'd never steal from Diego.

19:03.059 --> 19:06.396
Of course not, no one is saying that.
Diego didn't say anything.

19:06.479 --> 19:08.815
I'm worried. I'm just asking, that's all.

19:11.734 --> 19:13.736
Streaks are like that, you know?

19:14.821 --> 19:17.532
Sometimes they're good investments,
but not always.

19:17.991 --> 19:21.452
It's important not to put
all your eggs in the same basket.

19:22.453 --> 19:23.413
Yes.

19:24.372 --> 19:25.373
Maybe.

19:31.087 --> 19:32.380
Are you hungry?

19:34.924 --> 19:36.050
- Run! Run!
- Hey!

19:36.134 --> 19:38.553
- Son of a bitch.
- Fucking money-grabber!

19:38.636 --> 19:40.513
- What are you doing?
- Barca pays you!

19:40.597 --> 19:42.974
Go to Germany and you're dead!
Son of a bitch!

19:43.057 --> 19:45.393
- Diego, no!
- Come here, I'll kill you!

